ce:section.ce:para:
To gain more insight into the effects of low-temperature treatment of pure ZnO ETLs on PSC stability and performance, a planar device composed of FTO/ZnO/CH3NH3PbI3/carbon is constructed. Additionally, various quantum dots, including nH-CQDs, E-CQDs, and W-CQDs, are synthesized, and the J-V properties as shown in Fig. 11a. It is observed that all the samples exhibited nearly the same open-circuit voltage (V

                           oc
                        ) of ~0.85 V when no load is applied. The short-circuit current density (J

                           sc
                        ) of the device without carbon dots is measured at 14.42 mA/cm2. However, when quantum dots are decorated into the ZnO layer, the Jsc values gradually increase, indicating enhanced solar cell efficiency. The order of the Jsc values is nH-CQDs < E-CQDs < W-CQDs, with corresponding values of 15.19, 17.17, and 17.49 mA/cm2, respectively. Similarly, the power conversion efficiency of the solar cells followed the order of 10.04 % (nH-CQDs) < 11.43 % (E-CQDs) < 11.71 % (W-CQDs). Notably, the W-CQD-based perovskite solar cells demonstrated the highest efficiency among all the devices, both with and without CQDs.
